pecuniary (pi-KYOO-nee-er-ee) adjective

   1. Relating to money.

   2. Involving a monetary fine.

[Latin pecuniarius, from pecunia, property, wealth, derivative of pecus,
cattle.]

WordPix: http://wordsmith.org/words/pecuniary.gif

   "When asked why he held up the bank, the robber replied, `Because that's
   where pecuniary objects are.'"

This week's theme: WordPix, words drawn so that they explain themselves.

